The paper deals with privacy concerns in regression analysis of sensitive medical data, which falls under the category of security and privacy (cs.CR). The paper proposes solutions for differential privacy protection in regression analysis, which involves machine learning techniques such as empirical risk minimization (cs.LG) and Markov Chain Monte Carlo (cs.DS). The paper also deals with data sampling techniques (cs.DB) and information theory (cs.IT) in the context of privacy protection.
